Security Consultant at Pinkertons Fortune 500 client
Posted by: Pinkertons Fortune 500 client
Posted date: 05-May
Job Description:Competencies:
Ability to lead a team in analytical planning, critical review, and problem solving.
Excellent English oral and written communication skills required for preparing clear, concise, grammatically correct materials and communicating information effectively to others.
Good understanding and experience of project management.
Solid understanding of security operations, design, and systems integration.
Experience with multi-tasking and fast paced work environments.
Ability to prioritise workload is essential to ensure meeting client deadlines.
Action oriented with a passion for getting things done quickly, efficiently, and properly.
Ability to maintain professional composure when dealing with unusual and stressful circumstances.
Strong customer service and service delivery orientation.
Ability to interact effectively at all levels and across diverse cultures.
Strong cross-group collaboration and relationship management skills including directing & coordinating virtual teams to achieve deliverables.
Must be I.T literate and proficient.
Must be proficient and familiar in the use of Company Office products.
Must be proficient in the use of AutoCAD LT for creation and manipulation of 2D security layout designs.
Knowledge of local code/regulation/legislation knowledge for ASIA a plus Candidates must be able to meet the required security screening requirements as appropriate for this role.
Minimum qualifications and experience:
5+ years of experience in a Security Consulting Role - managing the deployment of physical security systems.
5+ Year experience in the design and/or installation of integrated electronic security systems, preferably gained in an engineering capacity.
PMP, CPP, PSP or CSPM certifications are highly desirable.
BS or BA in security or business or engineering related discipline, or equivalent experience preferred.
Technical competency with the technical solutions specified.
Subject matter expert in electronic physical security.Desired Candidate ProfileCompetencies:
